        "description": "30 kHz balances cleaning speed with reduced heat buildup (high rates increase accumulation, risking tempered glass fracture); typical for 1064 nm cleaning of transparent substrates. Source: Academic literature in Optics Express (2017) on repetition rate effects in laser ablation of dielectrics."
