        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 1000,
        "unit": "ns",
        "value": 10,
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred over picosecond/femtosecond for cost-effective cleaning with minimal heat-affected zone (HAZ <10 μm); 10 ns recommended for tempered glass to selectively ablate contaminants without inducing subsurface stress. Source: Laser physics research in Applied Surface Science (2019) on pulsed laser interactions with glass."
      },
      "scanSpeed": {
        "min": 10,
        "max": 5000,
        "value": 1000,
        "unit": "mm/s",
        "description": "Slower speeds for heavy contamination (e.g., oils/residues) ensure complete removal; 1000 mm/s optimal for light contaminants on tempered glass to balance efficiency and minimize heat accumulation. Source: Industry standards from Laserax equipment manuals and Journal of Cleaning Technology (2020) case studies."
